'''Capisterre''' (a [[corruption (grammar)|corruption]] of the original [[French language|French]] name '''Capesterre''') is a region covering the Northern Coastal plain on the Island of [[Saint Kitts]]. It was originally colonized by the [[French people|French]] in the early 17th century, with its capital on the only [[harbour]], in the fishing town of [[Dieppe Bay Town, Saint Kitts and Nevis|Dieppe]]. The area was lost to the [[Kingdom of Great Britain|British]] in 1713. Significant numbers of French immigrants from the neighbouring island of [[Saint-Barthélemy|Saint Barths]] came to Capisterre in the early 20th century, and became infamous for their illegal [[moonshine]] trade.

The region is home to the community festival [[La festival de Capisterre| La Festival de Capisterre]] which takes place every September during the week of [[Saint Kitts and Nevis]] independence (September 19th).

