'''Užička Crna Gora''' ({{lang-sr-cyr|Ужичка Црна Гора}}, "Black Mountains of Užice") is a mountainous region in western [[Serbia]] around the town of [[Užice]]. To the east lies [[Šumadija]]; Užička Crna Gora borders to the region of [[Rudnik (mountain)|Rudnik]], which lies in Šumadija, however, the border between the two is unclear due to historical administrative changes.<ref name="Живанчевић">{{cite book|author=Владимир Живанчевић|title=Гласник Етнографског музеја у Београду књ. 26|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=uhWzCAAAQBAJ&pg=PA160|publisher=Etnografski muzej u Beogradu|pages=160–|id=GGKEY:SW93K9QPS7K}}</ref>

