{{Infobox feature on celestial object |name = Yalode |image = File:Yalode crater.jpg |caption = |type = Crater |location = [[Ceres (dwarf planet)|Ceres]] |coordinates= {{coord|42.23|S|290.64|E|globe:ceres_type:landmark|display=inline,title}} |coordinates_footnotes = |diameter = 271 km |depth = |eponym = Yalodé, [[Dahomeyan mythology|Dahomeyan]] ([[Fon people|Fon]]) deity of the yam harvest }}
'''Yalode''' ({{IPAc-en|j|ə|ˈ|l|oʊ|d|i}})<ref>[https://ac.arc.nasa.gov/p52jvs37ff1/?launcher=false&fcsContent=true&pbMode=normal]</ref> is the largest confirmed crater on Ceres after [[Kerwan (crater)|Kerwan]]. It is adjacent to another large crater, [[Urvara (crater)|Urvara]]. It is named after the [[Dahomey]]an deity of the yam harvest, Yalodé. It appears to have a series of canyons running from it, in a northwestern direction. These may be ejecta from it. The canyons have been collectively named [[Samhain Catena]].
==See also== *[[List of geological features on Ceres]] *[[Dawn (spacecraft)|''Dawn'' (spacecraft)]], the spacecraft used to discover Yalode crater
